<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<LinearLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:orientation="vertical"
    xmlns:card_view="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"

    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:background="#fff"
    android:layout_margin="5dp">



    <ScrollView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:scrollbars="none"
        android:scrollbarSize="0dp"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        android:id="@+id/scrollView"
        android:layout_gravity="center_vertical" >


            <LinearLayout
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:orientation="vertical"
                android:layout_margin="5dp">
                >

                <TextView
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:text="'At bottom, robotics is about us. It is the discipline of emulating our lives, of wondering how we work.'"
                    android:textStyle="italic"
                    android:gravity="center"
                    android:textSize="15dp"
                    android:textColor="#000"
                    />
                <TextView
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:text="- ROD GRUPEN"
                    android:textStyle="bold"
                    android:gravity="right"
                    android:textSize="15dp"
                    android:textColor="#000"
                    />
                <TextView
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:text="\n\t\tOften in real life problems, neither a completely manual nor a complete automation will lead to a feasible solution. That is why we always need a semi-autonomous solution. Here is a semi-autonomous robotic event with both manual and autonomous operations within the bot. Welcome to the semi-autonomous event of K!15 'Hawker Bot'.
\n\n\t\tHey Sergeant, suit up. History taught us trouncing a kingdom is not an easy task. In this modern tough battle of kurukshetra you are about to strive hard to catch a throne by demolishing the domicile of your traducer. Yes you are going to fly in a Hawker to register your name in history. This edition of K! 15 will give you a first hand experience of being in a Warfield. Come on, let us fly!!!
\n\n\t\tYour Hawker moves slow, steady, peacefully, flying over the Kingdom of Iseac. Rebellions of Iseac do not know that they are destined to shatter their towns of Onos, Dovim fields, wealthy treysus, mighty patru and at last the capital Belkimort. Hawker is alloyed with vengeance, honour and intelligence to devastate. Make a counter attack and blast the foe’s empire.
\n\n\t\tLet‘s drop some lead on those villains!!!\n"


                    android:textSize="15dp"
                    android:textColor="#000"
                    />
            </LinearLayout>


    </ScrollView>

</LinearLayout>
